Sankofa — Agentic SOC Triage for Splunk
========================================

Installation:
1. Upload sankofa.spl via Splunk Web -> Apps -> Install from file
2. Configure the Sankofa backend (see main README.md)
3. Set SPLUNK_TOKEN in backend/.env to a token with search permissions
4. Start the backend: uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8001
5. Start the frontend: npm run dev

Saved Searches (auto-fire alerts to Sankofa):
- Sankofa - Detect Brute Force (every 5min)
- Sankofa - Detect Lateral Movement (every 5min)
- Sankofa - Detect LSASS Access (every 2min)
- Sankofa - Detect C2 Beacon (every 10min)

Dashboard:
- Apps -> Sankofa SOC Triage -> Dashboard

Architecture:
- Sankofa polls Splunk REST API every 30s for fired alerts
- High/critical alerts trigger 4 parallel subagents (Auth, Network, Endpoint, Lateral)
- Each subagent uses Splunk MCP Server to generate SPL from natural language
- Claude AI synthesizes findings into kill chain + confidence score + containment steps
- Analysts approve/dismiss containment actions via the React dashboard
